'''Christos V. Konstantakopoulos''' is a [[Greek]] [[film producer]] and writer working in Faliro House Productions. He began producing in [[2009 in film|2009]], and in [[2011]] he served as executive producer in [[Jeff Nichols]]' ''[[Take Shelter]]''. In [[2013]] he produced [[Richard Linklater]]'s ''[[Before Midnight (film)|Before Midnight]]'', the third entry of the ''Before'' trilogy, for which he has been nominated for several awards. He will make his screenwriting debut in [[2014]] with Yannis Economides' ''Mikro psari''. Among his upcoming works as producer or executive producer are [[Terrence Malick]]'s ''[[Knight of Cups (film)|Knight of Cups]]'' and an [[Untitled Terrence Malick project|untitled project]], and [[Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]-selected ''[[Only Lovers Left Alive]]''.

